 According to Sgt. Thabitha Leshilo, Mhluzi police spokesperson, the accident occurred on Friday afternoon at around 15:00. The driver of the BMW allegedly lost control of and the car slid sideways into an oncoming Toyota pickup. The BMW allegedly carried six people, who were scholars on their way to a dance. They were on their way from Mhluzi to Aerorand. Four people were killed and the remaining occupants of the BMW were taken to hospital in a critical condition. A case of culpable homicide has been opened. Sgt. Leshilo said that police are still investigating the matter. An image of the Toyota that was involved in the crash.  Dullstroom farm attack trial postponed Middelburg weekly weather forecast Pay or use ‘The road where death lives’  • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za 